<ns6527:section xmlns:ns6527="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.vi.loading">

  <ns6528:title xmlns:ns6528="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Loading a file into a buffer</ns6528:title>
  <ns6529:para xmlns:ns6529="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    To load a new file into the active window, use the following command:
    <ns6530:cmdsynopsis xmlns:ns6530="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns6531:command xmlns:ns6531="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
:n &lt;filename&gt;      
    </ns6531:command></ns6530:cmdsynopsis>
    If the window is a view onto a buffer which has changed since the last save, 
    <ns6532:emphasis xmlns:ns6532="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Vi</ns6532:emphasis> will force you to either
    <ns6533:itemizedlist xmlns:ns6533="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns6534:listitem xmlns:ns6534="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns6535:para xmlns:ns6535="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        save the current buffer via <ns6536:command xmlns:ns6536="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">:w</ns6536:command>, or to
      </ns6535:para></ns6534:listitem>
      <ns6537:listitem xmlns:ns6537="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns6538:para xmlns:ns6538="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        discard the current buffer via <ns6539:command xmlns:ns6539="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">:q!</ns6539:command>.  
      </ns6538:para></ns6537:listitem>
    </ns6533:itemizedlist>
  </ns6529:para>
</ns6527:section>